---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const interestEmail = "experiential.education.pdx@gmail.com";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Number Garden"
  description="Joyful mathematics for curious minds. The Number Garden is a warm, inquiry-driven math studio rooted in play, wonder, and deep thinking."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Opening soon</p>
      <h1>Joyful mathematics for curious minds.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        The Number Garden is a curated learning environment for children,
        families, and communities who want mathematics to feel alive: playful,
        rigorous, beautiful, and full of genuine discovery.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button button-primary" href="/about/">
          Read more
        </a>
        <a
          class="button button-secondary"
          href={`mailto:${interestEmail}?subject=The%20Number%20Garden%20interest`}
        >
          Join the interest list
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="hero-card" aria-label="What grows at The Number Garden">
      <p class="card-label">What grows here</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Rich problems worth lingering over</li>
        <li>Play, patterns, conjectures, and proof</li>
        <li>Challenge without hurry or coercion</li>
        <li>Serious mathematical joy</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-accent">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Idea</p>
      <h2>A garden is not built by force.</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="supporting-copy">
      There are many ways to grow a garden and many ways to grow human beings.
      One approach relies on control, uniformity, and pressure. Another
      nurtures the conditions in which life can thrive. The Number Garden is
      built around that second vision.
    </p>
    <p class="supporting-copy">
      We do not believe deep learning comes from rows of desks, compliance, or
      forced performance. We believe it emerges when children are invited into
      an environment rich enough, beautiful enough, and alive enough that they
      lose themselves in joyful problem solving.
    </p>
    <div class="inline-links">
      <a class="card-link" href="/about/">About the approach</a>
      <a class="card-link" href="/founder/">Meet the founder</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-light">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">A Real Place</p>
      <h2>Taking root in Hollywood, Portland.</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="supporting-copy">
      The first Number Garden space will live in Portland&apos;s Hollywood
      neighborhood, at 4152 NE Sandy Blvd. The philosophy is not floating in
      the abstract anymore. It is beginning to take shape in a real place.
    </p>
    <p class="supporting-copy">
      For now, this site is an invitation into the thinking behind the project:
      why it exists, how learning happens here, and what kind of mathematical
      culture it hopes to cultivate.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-dark">
    <div class="quote-block">
      <p class="quote-mark">"</p>
      <p class="quote">
        The way mathematicians use definitions, conjectures, and proofs is the
        most fun game I can possibly imagine.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="panel panel-light contact-panel">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Stay in Touch</p>
      <h2>The project is still taking root.</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="contact-copy">
      If this way of thinking about mathematics resonates with you, I would
      love to hear from you. Families, collaborators, educators, and kindred
      spirits are all welcome to reach out.
    </p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="contact-link" href="/contact/">
        Say hello
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
